  "body": "Dear React developers and community. Can anyone please explain to me why React throws a hard error if I use setState (or anything that entails setting new state, e.g. replaceState) if setState should work ONLY on a mounted component? If it never works with unmounted component, than what's the harm in using console.warn instead? Because in ALL our code we must use this.isMounted() && this.setState() â€” which is completely redundant.\n\nCan you please provide an explanation for this? Can you allow using a certain init option for not throwing this error?\n",
